   152→  "text": "The Android View rendering pipeline consists of a coordinated sequence of components that work together to measure, layout, and draw the view hierarchy to the screen.

## Key Components:

### 1. ViewRootImpl (core/java/android/view/ViewRootImpl.java)
The bridge between the window manager and the view hierarchy. ViewRootImpl.scheduleTraversals() (line 2948) is called whenever views need to be redrawn. This schedules a traversal callback that eventually calls performTraversals() (line 3422), which orchestrates the measure, layout, and draw passes. doTraversal() (line 2968) is the callback that executes the scheduled traversals.

### 2. Choreographer (core/java/android/view/Choreographer.java)
Provides VSYNC-driven frame scheduling. The doFrame() method (line 853) is called on each VSYNC signal, coordinating the timing of animations, input, and drawing. scheduleVsyncLocked() (line 1059) ensures frame callbacks are synchronized with the display's vertical synchronization to achieve smooth 60 FPS rendering.

### 3. View Measurement and Layout (core/java/android/view/View.java)
View.measure() (line 28137) determines the size of a view based on layout constraints. This calls the protected onMeasure() method (line 28269) which subclasses override to define their measurement logic. View.layout() (line 25385) positions the view within its parent, calling the protected onLayout() method (line 25502) for subclasses to position children. View.draw() (line 24849) renders the view to a canvas.

### 4. ThreadedRenderer (core/java/android/view/ThreadedRenderer.java)
Extends HardwareRenderer and proxies rendering calls to a dedicated render thread. The draw() method (line 795) receives the view hierarchy and initiates the GPU-accelerated rendering process by creating display lists from the view tree.

### 5. HardwareRenderer (graphics/java/android/graphics/HardwareRenderer.java)
Base class for hardware-accelerated rendering. syncAndDraw() (line 454) synchronizes the render thread state with the UI thread and initiates drawing. syncAndDrawFrame() (line 485) is the main entry point that coordinates GPU rendering of the entire frame.

### 6. RecordingCanvas (graphics/java/android/graphics/RecordingCanvas.java)
Records draw operations for deferred GPU rendering. The obtain() method (line 62) acquires a canvas from the pool to begin recording. finishRecording() (line 84) completes the recording and submits the display list to the GPU. RecordingCanvas internally uses a native DisplayListCanvas (line 275: nCreateDisplayListCanvas) which bridges to the native GPU rendering implementation.

## Rendering Pipeline Flow:

1. ViewRootImpl.scheduleTraversals() schedules a traversal when view state changes
2. Choreographer.doFrame() coordinates with VSYNC to schedule frame callbacks
3. ViewRootImpl.performTraversals() executes the three-phase traversal:
   - Measure: View.measure() computes view dimensions
   - Layout: View.layout() positions views in the hierarchy
   - Draw: View.draw() records drawing operations
4. ThreadedRenderer.draw() initiates GPU-accelerated rendering
5. HardwareRenderer.syncAndDrawFrame() synchronizes and submits frames
6. RecordingCanvas records draw operations that are replayed on the GPU
7. DisplayListCanvas (native) executes GPU commands for final rasterization"
